snippet.textDisplay: Andy Tate - One of the few sane voices left amongst the United fans airing their views on YouTube. Another one is Sam from United Peoples TV. People say the job may be too big for a manager, I feel it also applies to some fans for whom the task of supporting the club is a bit too much. They can't handle the stress that comes from inconsistent performances especially when they're living in the past glory days. Time to wake up and give support to Ole at least until the end of the season. Then we can make our minds up whether to move on from him or stay put. What's the point of being in the Champions League next season if you're not gonna win it anyway. Yes, you can attract better players with UCL football but a club of United's stature can still attract players. All that is required is smart decisions rather than desperate measures. Last but not the least, the win against Spurs may provide a false sense of comfort to some fans who are already expecting a win on Saturday. Might just end up being a wake up call. United are currently where they deserve to be. Results against big teams are the little bits of positivity that we keep clinging onto. Keeps the media pressure away from the manager while things keep rolling in the background.

snippet.textDisplay:
We do well against the big teams and drop points against the lower half.
We need some more creativity in the midfield to hit those game breaking passes. And for that to be possible we need some attacking midfielders and strikers with clever movment to create space for eachother to make deep runs and take those gamebreaking passes all the way to the net. I think we have a few of those with James and Rashford, maby even Lingard if he can get his shit togther.


Scott is a warrior and a godsend for the team I just hope Pogba can deliver the creativity we need and even if he can we still need another midfielder to bolster the ranks. The stable atm is fragile and unstable, and Fred and Pereira are just not good enugh. Neighter is Matic tbh but i guess we'll find out if he can step it up when he comes back. We also need a Van Nistelrooy type player (kinda like Lukaku used to be) to break those damn deadlock games where teams are deffending with 12 men. United atm is too dependent on space to run and pass the ball. They don't always have the option when teams are laying low and they usually struggle when faced with this scenario. We also need a right winger but one thing at the time i guess :p


Hoping Erling Braut Haaland can be the new Van Nistelrooy. He's strong, fast, a fenomenal finisher. And he's 19 years old.


Good things ahead! Exciting times to be a Manu fan (^^)

snippet.textDisplay: This was a one off performance I'll have to admit. Players played for the manager and it showed from the off. Did we deserve to win? More than Spurs yes but lets not get carried away, our goals came from a howler and a dubious penalty. I don't want us to stick with Ole and end up mid-table ' because we're building something',  countless managers have rebuilt squads while putting in consistent performances and still finishing in the top 4. I do not feel confident that we'll achieve that with Ole and regardless of the result this weekend we will continue to throw away points to lesser teams due to the lack of tactica and responsibility from the management team.
